## Styling Approach

- **Tailwind for styling** - Use Tailwind utility classes, not CSS files
- **shadcn components** - Use components from `@/components/ui/` for consistent design
- **No inline styles** - Never use `style` prop; use Tailwind classes
- **Responsive design** - Use Tailwind responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)

## shadcn Components

- **Card components** - Use `<Card>`, `<CardHeader>`, `<CardContent>`, `<CardFooter>` for containers
- **Form components** - Use `<Form>`, `<FormField>`, `<FormItem>`, `<FormLabel>`, `<FormControl>`, `<FormMessage>`
- **Button variants** - Use Button with variants: `default`, `outline`, `ghost`, `link`, `destructive`
- **Input components** - Use `<Input>` and `<Label>` from ui components
- **Icons from lucide-react** - Use Lucide icons (e.g., `<UserIcon />`)

## Layout Patterns

- **Flexbox and Grid** - Use Tailwind flex/grid utilities for layouts
- **Spacing** - Use consistent spacing scale: `gap-4`, `gap-6`, `p-4`, `m-4`
- **Centering** - Use `flex items-center justify-center` for centering
- **Max width containers** - Use `max-w-sm`, `max-w-md`, etc. for content width

## Component Composition

- **Spread props** - Spread field props from react-hook-form: `{...field}`
- **asChild pattern** - Use `asChild` prop to compose components (e.g., `<Button asChild>`)
- **Conditional classes** - Use `className` with template strings for conditional classes

## Accessibility

- **Semantic HTML** - Use proper HTML elements (`<button>`, `<input>`, `<label>`)
- **Form labels** - Always associate labels with inputs
- **Button types** - Specify `type="button"`, `type="submit"` explicitly
- **Alt text** - Provide `alt` attributes for images
